    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-12-13T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-12-13T13:00:00-05:00" n="363"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d363">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/7128: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Fish</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-12-13T20:00:00+02:00"
                            >December 13, 1940—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 13—7:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>349. For Miles, War Department, from Fellers:<note n="23" xml:id="d363fn23">Maj.
                        Bonner Frank Fellers, Military Attaché in Egypt.</note>
                    <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“1805: British General Headquarters confidentially discloses that the
                            Italian western desert air force is practically grounded. First and
                            Second Libyan and First and Fourth Blackshirt Divisions have been
                            annihilated. 62nd and Catanzaro Divisions are now in Bardia area.
                            Retreating 63rd Division has been attacked by R.A.F. with British
                            mechanized force in pursuit. Prisoners estimated at 30,000, British
                            losses light. Heavy sandstorm intensifies battle confusion.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fish</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
